s:49:"JOIN THE HURT FOOT FITNESS COACHING PROGRAM HERE.";i:2;s:102:"Do you have an injury or recovering from injury or surgery and cant practice standing yoga on the mat.";i:3;s:31:"Chair yoga might be the answer.";i:4;s:52:"Chair yoga is accessible and inclusive form of yoga.";i:5;s:82:"It includes all the elements of mat yoga it has the same energy flow and benefits.";i:6;s:55:"The whole practice can be conducted in seated position.";i:7;s:73:"Try these 7 chair yoga poses to compensate for your foot or ankle injury.";i:8;s:88:"For this sequence you will need two chairs of the same height a yoga block and a pillow.";i:9;s:83:"Warrior 2 Virabhadrasana 2 Warrior 2 is both a strengthening and a stretching pose.";i:10;s:126:"This variation will reduce the pressure on your hips knees ankles and feet making it a great option for yoga with your injury.";i:11;s:14:"Let us try it.";i:12;s:120:"This variation decreases pressure on your hips knees ankles and feet making it a great option for yoga with your injury.";i:13;s:136:"Sit sideways on your chair with your right thigh and butt cheek on the chair but your left leg and cheek just off the edge of the chair.";i:14;s:78:"Try These 7 Chair Yoga Poses to Help Compensate for Your Foot or Ankle Injury.";i:15;s:84:"For this sequence youll need two chairs of equal height a yoga block and one pillow.";i:16;s:81:"Warrior 2 Virabhadrasana 2 Warrior 2 is both a strengthening and stretching pose.";i:17;s:120:"This variation decreases pressure on your hips knees ankles and feet making it a great option for yoga with your injury.";i:18;s:78:"Try These 7 Chair Yoga Poses to Help Compensate for Your Foot or Ankle Injury.";i:19;s:84:"For this sequence youll need two chairs of equal height a yoga block and one pillow.";i:20;s:81:"Warrior 2 Virabhadrasana 2 Warrior 2 is both a strengthening and stretching pose.";i:21;s:120:"This variation decreases pressure on your hips knees ankles and feet making it a great option for yoga with your injury.";i:22;s:33:"Below are chair yoga safety tips.";i:23;s:73:"Breathe - inhaling and exhaling with movement encourages joints to relax.";i:24;s:31:"Align the knee over your ankle.";i:25;s:33:"Keep your feet flat on the floor.";i:26;s:29:"Avoiding jerking or bouncing.";i:27;s:39:"What are the basic poses in chair yoga.";i:28;s:93:"Using a yoga strap in this pose helps to connect the hands important for energizing the arms.";i:29;s:25:"Begin in seated Tadasana.";i:30;s:50:"You may need to sit slightly forward in the chair.";i:31;s:61:"Align and ground down with the feet directly below the knees.";i:32;s:65:"Extend the left arm out in front of you turning the palm outward.";i:33;s:39:"Swing your arm around behind your back.";i:34;s:107:"Chair yoga is an ideal way to invigorate your mind and body from the comfort of your office or desk chairs.";i:35;s:227:"In as little as 5 to 7 minutes you can perform a handful of poses that will stimulate your circulation boost your metabolism lengthen your muscles deepen your breathing and fill you up with a surplus of life force energy Prana.";i:36;s:53:"For these reasons Chair Yoga is the perfect solution.";i:37;s:150:"Each of the included Yoga routines are gentle enough for anyone to complete and can easily be performed from any chair in 10 minutes or less each day.";i:38;s:48:"This comprehensive bundle includes 8 videos and.";i:39;s:74:"All Levels Chair Yoga Routine For Injury Disability Or Stretching At Work.";i:40;s:72:"Ground your mind and body with this short all levels Chair Yoga Routine.";i:41;s:123:"Perfect for all levels and abilities Chair Yoga a great way to relax from head to toe without the stress of weight bearing.";i:42;s:69:"This routine can help you stay active when recovering from an injury.";i:43;s:98:"For those with injuries trying yoga postures while sitting on the floor or a chair can be helpful.";i:44;s:61:"This allows the student to have more control and move slowly.";i:45;s:50:"Learning Yoga from Your Wheelchair or Power Chair.";i:46;s:110:"If you have a medical condition you may want to consult with your doctor before beginning any fitness program.";i:47;s:84:"While practicing Yoga when possible have an instructor caregiver or partner present.";i:48;s:64:"When stretching stretch to the point of mild tension never pain.";i:49;s:31:"Chair Yoga For Injury Benefits.";i:50;s:133:"Yoga has been shown to improve overall health prevent and even in some cases reverse disease when practiced regularly as a lifestyle.";i:51;s:104:"With this in mind its no surprise that it can therefore lend its benefits to those with mobility issues.";i:52;s:22:"Here are some of them.";i:53;s:70:"You can build strength and fitness from a regular Chair Yoga practice.";i:54;s:99:"It also reduces anxiety helps lower blood pressure protects joints and builds strength and balance.";i:55;s:103:"We found a fantastic 30 minute routine of gentle chair yoga for seniors thats free to watch on YouTube.";i:56;s:89:"Instructor Sherry Zak Morris makes the class fun and lively and explains the benefits of.";i:57;s:78:"Try These 7 Chair Yoga Poses to Help Compensate for Your Foot or Ankle Injury.";i:58;s:84:"For this sequence youll need two chairs of equal height a yoga block and one pillow.";i:59;s:81:"Warrior 2 Virabhadrasana 2 Warrior 2 is both a strengthening and stretching pose.";i:60;s:120:"This variation decreases pressure on your hips knees ankles and feet making it a great option for yoga with your injury.";i:61;s:24:"Chair Yoga Leg Sequence.";i:62;s:93:"Lift your right thigh a few inches and then straighten your knee extending your heel forward.";i:63;s:29:"Then drop your leg back down.";i:64;s:29:"Do the same on your left leg.";i:65;s:35:"Repeat four more times on each leg.";i:66;s:44:"On the last lift keep your thigh lifted and.";i:67;s:97:"Place your left hand on the back of the chair and step the right foot onto the seat of the chair.";i:68;s:40:"Next lift your right arm over your head.";i:69;s:37:"Hold and repeat on the opposite side.";i:70;s:32:"Yoga Exercises for Brain Injury.";i:71;s:120:"These are just a few examples of yoga poses for brain injury patients that will improve muscle coordination and balance.";i:72;s:59:"This leads many to yoga as a low-impact exercise trade-off.";i:73;s:86:"Research indicates yoga may improve overall leg strength which can benefit your knees.";i:74;s:75:"But certain postures might actually put extra stress on your knees as well.";i:75;s:121:"Check out these expert tips for modifying yoga with a knee injury so you can make it onto your mat without discomfort or.";i:76;s:22:"Yoga for Brain Injury.";i:77;s:52:"Yoga is more than just stretching and awkward poses.";i:78;s:86:"The practice of yoga incorporates the use of breath focus balance and muscle strength.";i:79;s:124:"As a therapy for both the mind and body yoga can bring a new focus of what one can achieve building optimism confidence and.";}}